    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>''We call young men living with their wives' families in urban areas apple polishers, meaning they are always trying to be more considerate of their wives' needs. If not, they risk being thrown out.''</p>
        <p>MASAHIRO YAMADA, a sociologist in Tokyo. [A4]</p>
